RefrigeratorApp
This is a simple console-based application that simulates a refrigerator.
Users can add new products,
consume existing products,
view the current status of the refrigerator,
and view the purchase history of each item.

Prerequisites
In order to run this application, you must have the following installed:

Java JDK (version 8 or higher)
Git


Installation

To install the application, follow these steps:

Clone this repository to your local machine using the following command:

git clone https://github.com/exampleuser/refrigerator-app.git

Navigate to the project directory:

cd refrigerator-app

Compile the Java code:

javac Main.java Refrigerator.java Product.java

Run the application:

java Main

Usage
Upon running the application, you will be presented with a main menu that lists the available options:

Insert a new product
Consume a product
Current status
Show purchase history
Exit

Insert a new product
To insert a new product, select option 1 from the main menu.You will be prompted to enter the
name of the product, the quantity,and the unit of measure (units, grams, or liters).

Consume a product
To consume an existing product, select option 2 from the main menu.
You will be prompted to enter the name of the product and the quantity you wish to consume.

Current status
To view the current status of the refrigerator, select option 3 from the main menu.
This will display a list of all the products in the refrigerator along with their quantities.

Show purchase history
To view the purchase history of each item in the refrigerator, select option 4 from the main menu.
This will display a list of all the products in the refrigerator along with their purchase history.

Exit
To exit the application, select option 5 from the main menu.

